Defendant in custody.    
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for seven (7) years.   Three (3) years initial confinment, followed by four (4) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend one (1) year in Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately.  Transfer to Milwaukee County is authorized as long as there is no electronic monitoring.   
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Submit random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Maintain full-time employment or school or combination; 
6) No contact with co-defendant, Winfield Waak, without prior agent approval;
7) Submit DNA sample;
8) Pay costs of action; 
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Defendant is given 258 days sentence credit.  
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
